This tool pulls data from financialmodelingprep.com and stores it in a local database.
You need an API-key for this to work. You can add your key into the core.py file.

Currently supported data:
    -historical minute data

All the functionality is written into core.py

How to use:
    1: Run initiate.py to create the database and the core tables that data is stored into
    2: Enter all the stocks you want to watch into the tickers list of sample_populate.py
    3: Regularily run update.py to get new stock data entered into the database. Automation for this taks is advised (Windows Task Scheduler or similar)